.TH "pci_rebar_set_size" 9 "pci_rebar_set_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_rebar_set_size \- set a new size for a BAR
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_rebar_set_size
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "int bar "  ","
.BI "int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
PCI device
.IP "bar" 12
BAR to set size to
.IP "size" 12
new size as defined in the spec (0=1MB, 19=512GB)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the new size of a BAR as defined in the spec.
Returns zero if resizing was successful, error code otherwise.
